ENTRY       EC 1.1.1.183                Enzyme
NAME        geraniol dehydrogenase (NADP+)
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     geraniol:NADP+ oxidoreductase
REACTION    geraniol + NADP+ = geranial + NADPH + H+ [RN:R03581]
ALL_REAC    R03581;
            (other) R08083 R08084 R08085
SUBSTRATE   geraniol [CPD:C01500];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006]
PRODUCT     geranial [CPD:C01499];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     Also acts, more slowly on farnesol but not on nerol. The enzyme produces a mixture known as citral, which includes geranial and neral. It is still not known whether neral is produced directly by the enzyme, or by isomerization of geranial.
